Antimicrobial assayed for resistance for the factor in question

Contingency Table: # AMR- in exposed group

Contingency Table: # AMR- in referent group
Prevalence Table: % AMR+ in exposed group
Prevalence Table: % AMR- in exposed group
Prevalence Table: % AMR+ in referent group
Prevalence Table: % AMR- in referent group
Total # [res_unit] in exposed group
Total # [res_unit] in referent group
Odds Ratio: Odds ratio value for the factor
Odds Ratio: Lower bound of the confidence interval
Odds Ratio: Upper bound of the confidence interval
Odds Ratio: Significance value (p-value)
Odds Ratio: The confidence interval (i.e. 95%)
Meta-analysis: ID of the meta-analysis group to which the factor belongs (if applicable)
Meta-analysis: antimicrobial/class of antimicrobials to which resistance was assayed in the factors included in this particular meta-analysis group (if applicable)
Meta-analysis: type/level of granularity of this particular meta-analysis group (i.e. within studies, across studies) (if applicable)
If TRUE, factor was excluded from calculations by sawmill due to errors/missing data
Accompanying reason for factors with exclude_sawmill = TRUE
Set of result fields provided in the study (i.e. if A, B, C, and D are provided, the grain is con_table_pos_neg)
If TRUE, at least one of A, B, C, or D is less than or equal to the low_cell_threshold and a correction factor was applied to A, B, C, and D
If TRUE, both A and C are equal to 0 (meaning that no AMR+ observations were made)
If TRUE, the grain is prev_table_pos_tot and the values in the prevalence table do not add up to 100 where they should
Final odds ratio (either copied from odds field if provided, or calculated)
Standard error of the log(odds ratio)
Significance value (p-value, either copied from oddsig field if the grain is odds_ratio, or calculated for other grains)
Log of the final odds ratio
URL to the reference study
HTML link to the reference study
